The paper deals with the problem of demand private coded caching, which involves designing caching and delivery schemes that satisfy a privacy requirement. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) as it involves optimizing the transmission rate in a noiseless broadcast network. It also involves designing efficient data structures (cs.DS) for caching and delivery. Privacy is a key concern in this problem, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also proposes an achievable scheme and compares its performance with existing lower bounds, which involves analyzing the complexity and efficiency of algorithms (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of optimizing the transmission rate under privacy constraints, which is related to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
